\id 2PE - Plain English Version
\h 2 Peter
\toc3 2 Peter
\toc2 2 Peter
\toc1 Peter’s 2nd Letter
\mt1 The 2nd letter that Peter wrote
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk 2 Peter\bk*)
\imt1 About this letter
\ip Peter was one of Jesus’s 12 special workers. He went everywhere with Jesus and knew him well.
\ip Peter wrote 2 letters that are now in the Holy Bible. This is the 2nd letter. He wrote it about 2,000 years ago, about 30 years after Jesus went back to heaven.
\ip In this letter Peter told Christians how to become strong for Jesus. And he told them about people that reckon they were saying God’s words, but they were lying. And he wrote about what it will be like in the last days of this world, before God finishes it up.
\ip These words that Peter wrote have very important messages for all of us Christians.
\cl Chapter
\c 1
\p 
